+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QP48nTtiNQ85K8Kn7fgNZQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me compile and present a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── types.ts          # Type definitions\n│       ├── index.ts          # Public exports\n│       ├── engine.ts         # BuildEngine class (DAG plugin system)\n│       └── templates.ts      # Default and list templates\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep          # (empty - plugins to be implemented)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts          # Core engine tests\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── dev-server.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── rss-feed.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Core Type System (`src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**SiteConfig Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n**ContentFile Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**BuildContext Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\n\n**Plugin Hooks Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Plugin Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\n\n**Template Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Plugin Registration**: `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` and `registerTemplate(template: Template)`\n- **Topological Sort**: `resolvePluginOrder()` - Implements DAG-based plugin dependency resolution with circular dependency detection\n- **Build Lifecycle**:\n  1. Resolves plugin order using topological sort\n  2. Executes all `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  3. Applies all `transformContent` hooks to each file in plugin order\n  4. Renders content using registered templates\n  5. Executes all `afterBuild` hooks in order\n\n**Template Rendering:**\n- Uses `template.render(content, data)` for each file\n- Default template name is 'default' if not specified\n- Falls back to raw content if no matching template exists\n- Template data includes: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, file metadata, `siteTitle`, `baseUrl`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Templates (`src/core/templates.ts`)\n\n**Default Template** (name: 'default'):\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n    ${data.date ? `<time>${data.date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**List Template** (name: 'list'):\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (`tests/core.test.ts`) - 15 Test Cases\n\n1. **Plugin registration** - Verifies plugins can be registered\n2. **Template registration** - Verifies templates can be registered\n3. **Default template rendering** - HTML output structure and content inclusion\n4. **List template rendering** - Renders with list wrapper div\n5. **No template fallback** - Raw content output when template not found\n6. **beforeBuild hook** - Called during build process\n7. **transformContent hook** - Files are transformed in order\n8. **afterBuild hook** - Called after rendering\n9. **Plugin execution order** - Respects dependency declarations (topological sort)\n10. **Circular dependency detection** - Throws error for circular deps\n11. **Missing dependency detection** - Throws error for missing deps\n12. **Multiple plugins transformContent** - Applied sequentially, output chained\n13. **Shared data store** - ctx.data accessible across plugins\n14. **Metadata retention** - File metadata, dates, tags preserved through build\n15. **Empty file list** - Handles empty input gracefully\n\n---\n\n### 6. Required Plugin Implementations\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext** (`src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- Convert basic markdown to HTML (headings, bold)\n- Footnote syntax `[^1]` with supercript link to `#fn-1`\n- Footnote section rendering with `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n- Admonition containers: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n- Preserve existing HTML in content\n- Handle empty content\n- Should use `marked` library for markdown parsing\n\n**Export:** `createMarkdownExtPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 2: taxonomy** (`src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- **beforeBuild hook:**\n  - Build tag index from file tags\n  - Store as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n  - Tags normalized to lowercase\n  - Handle files without tags\n  - Handle empty file list\n  \n- **afterBuild hook:**\n  - Generate tag listing pages at `tags/{tag}.html`\n  - Each page lists all files with that tag\n  \n- Store the tag map in `ctx.data` for access by other plugins (e.g., RSS)\n\n**Export:** `createTaxonomyPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 3: syntax-highlight** (`src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- Process `<pre><code class=\"language-{lang}\">` blocks\n- Add `highlighted` class to code element\n- Add `data-language=\"{lang}\"` attribute to `<pre>` tag\n- Handle multiple code blocks in one file\n- Skip code blocks without language class\n- Preserve code block content\n- Handle empty code blocks\n- **Not** modify inline `<code>` tags (only `<pre><code>` blocks)\n\n**Export:** `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 4: search-index** (`src/plugins/search-index.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- **afterBuild hook:**\n  - Generate `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n  - Array of entries with: `{ slug, title, content, tags? }`\n  - Strip HTML tags from content (extract plain text)\n  - Include code block content\n  - Include tags if present\n  - Output is valid JSON\n  - Handle empty file list\n\n**Export:** `createSearchIndexPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 5: asset-pipeline** (`src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- **transformContent hook:**\n  - Rewrite relative image URLs `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n  - Rewrite relative link URLs `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n  - Leave absolute URLs (http/https) unchanged\n  - Skip already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs\n  - Build asset manifest in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n  - Manifest format: `{ assets: string[] }`\n  - Accumulate assets across multiple files\n  - Handle files with no asset references\n\n**Export:** `createAssetPipelinePlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 6: dev-server** (`src/plugins/dev-server.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (9 tests):**\n- **afterBuild hook:**\n  - Store config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n  - Config structure:\n    ```typescript\n    {\n      port: number;\n      routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n      assetPaths: string[];\n      searchIndexPath: string;\n    }\n    ```\n  - Default port: 3000\n  - Extract asset paths from `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` if present\n  - Create asset routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n  - Extract content routes from `ctx.output` (*.html files)\n  - Create static content routes with `handler: 'static'`\n  - Include search index path (if exists in output): `/search-index.json`\n  - Handle missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n**Export:** `createDevServerPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 7: sitemap** (`src/plugins/sitemap.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- **afterBuild hook:**\n  - Generate `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n  - Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...><urlset>...<url><loc>...</loc></url>...</urlset>`\n  - Include all content page URLs from `ctx.output` (*.html files)\n  - Include taxonomy tag page URLs from `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` paths\n  - Include feed.xml URL if present in output\n  - Build full URLs using `config.baseUrl`\n  - Handle sites with no tag pages\n  - Handle sites with no feed\n\n**Export:** `createSitemapPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 8: rss-feed** (`src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`)\n**Test Coverage (8 tests):**\n- **afterBuild hook:**\n  - Generate `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n  - Valid RSS 2.0 XML: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...><rss version=\"2.0\"><channel>...<item>...</item>...</channel></rss>`\n  - Feed items:\n    - Include HTML content in `<![CDATA[...]]>` wrapper\n    - Include category tags from `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n    - Include pubDate if file has date (skip if undefined)\n    - Include slug-based link URL: `${baseUrl}/{slug}.html`\n  - Channel:\n    - Title from `config.title`\n    - Link from `config.baseUrl`\n  - Sort items by date newest first\n  - Handle files without dates\n  - Handle files without tags\n\n**Export:** `createRssFeedPlugin(): Plugin`\n\n---\n\n### 7. package.json Configuration\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. tsconfig.json Configuration\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. vitest Configuration\n\n```typescript\n{\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Implementation Requirements\n\nYou need to create 8 plugin files in `/workspace/src/plugins/`:\n\n1. **markdown-ext.ts** - Markdown to HTML conversion with footnotes and admonitions\n2. **taxonomy.ts** - Tag indexing and tag page generation\n3. **syntax-highlight.ts** - Code block language and highlighting markers\n4. **search-index.ts** - JSON search index generation\n5. **asset-pipeline.ts** - Asset URL rewriting and manifest\n6. **dev-server.ts** - Dev server configuration generation\n7. **sitemap.ts** - XML sitemap generation\n8. **rss-feed.ts** - RSS 2.0 feed generation\n\n**Key Implementation Patterns:**\n- All plugins follow the `Plugin` interface with `name`, `version`, `dependencies`, and `hooks`\n- Plugins use the DAG system via the `dependencies` array for execution ordering\n- Shared data flows through `ctx.data` Map\n- Output files written to `ctx.output` Map\n- Content transformations in `transformContent` hook, post-build processing in `afterBuild` hook\n\nThis is a comprehensive static site generator toolkit with 8 specialized plugins that work together through a clean dependency graph system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abe4846 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34143\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 38604</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64da79a0-d75b-41db-a1c0-c69309d380c0","uuid":"201d0b42-3fa5-423b-a06b-66380b25c226","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. The contents of src/core/ (types.ts, build engine, templates)\n3. All test files in tests/plugins/ - read each one completely\n4. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n5. package.json and tsconfig.json\n6. Any existing plugin examples\n\nRead ALL files completely. This is critical for implementation.","agentId":"abe4846","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me compile and present a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── types.ts          # Type definitions\n│       ├── index.ts          # Public exports\n│       ├── engine.ts         # BuildEngine class (DAG plugin system)\n│       └── templates.ts      # Default and list templates\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep          # (empty - plugins to be implemented)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts          # Core engine tests\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── dev-server.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── rss-feed.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Core Type System (`src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**SiteConfig Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n**ContentFile Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**BuildContext Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\n\n**Plugin Hooks Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Plugin Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\n\n**Template Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Plugin Registration**: `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` and 